Preheat your oven to 200°C. Put the @ketjap manis{25%ml}, @soy sauce{25%ml}, @honey{15%g} and @rice vinegar{15%ml} in a #mixing bowl{}. Stir together, then add the @lamb mince{200%g} and mix with your hands until the meat and sauce are completely combined - wash your hands.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1%large}. Thinly slice the @chestnut mushrooms{150%g}. Separate the @broccoli{1} into florets (little trees). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Peel and grate the @ginger{1%thumb-sized piece}.

Pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a large #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add a pinch of @salt{pinch}, stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a #lid{} on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, add the broccoli to a large #baking tray{} drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat, then roast on the top shelf of your oven until tender but crispy, about ~{15%mins}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the mushrooms along with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Stir-fry until they are starting to brown, ~{3-4%mins}. Add the red onion, stir together and cook until the red onion has softened, ~{4-5%mins} more. Stir every minute. Add the ginger and garlic, stir fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the lamb to the veggies and cook until the lamb is completely browned, ~{4-5%mins}. Break it up with a #wooden spoon{} as it cooks. Once the lamb is browned, add the @water{25%ml}, stir together and cook until the lamb mixture is sticky and slightly saucy, ~{3-4%mins}. Meanwhile, roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch}(roughly chopped, stalks and all) and the @salted peanuts{25%g}(roughly chopped). Remove the lamb from the heat once cooked.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and spoon it into bowls. Top with the lamb, then the roasted broccoli and finish with a sprinkling of coriander and peanuts. Enjoy!